{"article_id":"kycephdHoGPbnNBe","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"While he now demands","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"that higher tax rates for the wealthy must be part of a \" fiscal cliff \" deal ,","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"President Obama took a very different line just over a year ago in the last major clash with Congress over a long-term budget deal .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"In comments","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"Republicans on Capitol Hill are highlighting ,","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"Mr. Obama argued in the summer of 2011","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"that the government could raise more than $ 1 trillion in revenue","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"without increasing tax rates","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"paid by the rich","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"- something","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"the president now contends","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"is mathematically impossible .","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"\" What we said was , give us $ 1.2 trillion in additional revenues ,","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"which could be accomplished","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"without hiking taxes","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"- tax rates -","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"but could simply be accomplished","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"by eliminating loopholes ,","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"eliminating some deductions","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"and engaging in a tax-reform process","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"that could have lowered rates generally","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"while broadening the base , \"","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"the president said at a July 22 , 2011 , White House news conference .","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"Mr. Obama ' s position today is that his $ 1.6 trillion plan","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"to avoid the fiscal cliff of tax increases and deep spending cuts","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"must include higher tax rates for the top 2 percent of the income scale .","depth":5},{"id":26,"text":"\" It ' s not me being stubborn .","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"It ' s not me being partisan .","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"It ' s just a matter of math , \"","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"Mr. Obama said this week in an interview with Bloomberg .","depth":4},{"id":30,"text":"During remarks to corporate CEOs at the Business Roundtable on Wednesday , Mr. Obama called on the leaders to urge Republicans to accept the tax-rate increases","depth":5},{"id":31,"text":"and not to use the debt ceiling","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"to gain leverage for more entitlement cuts in the fiscal-cliff negotiations .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"The president made the comments on a day","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"when he and House Speaker John A. Boehner , Ohio Republican , spoke by phone about a deal","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"to avoid the fiscal cliff .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"Aides to both men gave no details about the call ,","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"and no plans for a face-to-face meeting were announced .","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"Separately , Treasury Secretary Timothy F. Geithner was laying down a much tougher line","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"by saying","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"the administration was \" absolutely \" prepared to go over the fiscal cliff","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"if Republicans refuse to bend on higher tax rates for the wealthy .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"\" There ' s no prospect in an agreement","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"that doesn ' t involve those rates going up on the top 2 percent of the wealthiest Americans , \"","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"Mr. Geithner , one of the White House ' s lead negotiators in the talks , told CNBC in an interview .","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"His remarks drew an immediate rebuke from one key Republican .","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"\" This is one of the most stunning and irresponsible statements","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"I ' ve heard in some time , \"","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"said Sen. Orrin G. Hatch of Utah , the ranking Republican on the Senate Finance Committee .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"Republicans on Capitol Hill quickly denounced the statements from Mr. Obama on the debt ceiling ,","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"raising the federal government ' s borrowing limit is Congress ' job","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"and should remain so ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"despite Mr. Obama ' s proposal","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"to make it more difficult for lawmakers to block an increase .","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"\" The president wants to have the ability","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"to raise the debt ceiling","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"whenever he wants ,","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"for as much","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"as he wants ,","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"with no responsibility or spending cuts attached , \"","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"said Don Stewart , a spokesman for Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell , Kentucky Republican .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"\" This is an idea","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"opposed by Democrats and Republicans alike ;","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"it ' s a power grab","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"that has no support here . \"","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"Mr. Boehner ' s office on Wednesday was highlighting media reports on the White House ' s shifting line on tax increases ,","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"Mr. Obama ' s previous position aligned closely with the plan","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"House Republicans are offering .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Republicans have demonstrated","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"\" there is a middle-ground solution","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"that can cut spending","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"and bring in revenue","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"without hurting American small businesses , \"","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"Mr. Boehner said in a statement .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"\" It ' s a solution","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"President Obama himself once supported .","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"If the math worked in 2011 ,","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"why doesn ' t it work today ? \"","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"Mr. Obama didn ' t lay out the specifics of his 2011 plan at the time","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"-","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"exactly which deductions and loopholes he would target","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"to produce the revenue .","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"He is now criticizing Republicans","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"for failing to lay out the details of their plan .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"in making his offer to Mr. Obama this week ,","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"Mr. Boehner cited a nine-page report by the Committee for a Responsible Federal Budget , a nonpartisan , business-backed group","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"that provided three options","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"for finding the necessary revenue","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"by limiting deductions","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"without increasing tax rates .","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"White House officials said","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"Republicans are not telling the full story about Mr. Obama ' s 2011 quote .","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"The president ' s comment ,","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"they said ,","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"was part of an agreement with Republicans","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"to spend the next year","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"overhauling the tax code","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"to find additional revenue ,","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"and","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"if Washington couldn ' t get all the complex tax changes through Congress by the end of 2012 ,","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"tax rates on the top 2 percent of Americans would go up .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"Jason Furman , deputy director of the National Economic Council and an assistant to the president for economic policy , also said","depth":4},{"id":105,"text":"the White House has \" done a lot of work \" in the past year in crunching numbers","depth":5},{"id":106,"text":"and now \" knows more about tax reform \"","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"than it did in 2011 .","depth":6},{"id":108,"text":"\" We didn ' t sit here","depth":6},{"id":109,"text":"twiddling our thumbs , \"","depth":6},{"id":110,"text":"Mr. Furman told reporters during a briefing Wednesday .","depth":5},{"id":111,"text":"\" So just at a purely analytical level , we know more about tax reform ,","depth":6},{"id":112,"text":"we know more about tax expenditures ,","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"we know more about all of those topics now","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"than , we ' ve ,","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"you know ,","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"known before , \"","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"he said .","depth":5},{"id":118,"text":"One of the items","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"that the president ' s economic team evaluated","depth":6},{"id":120,"text":"was the idea","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"of capping deductions at $ 25,000 for all Americans .","depth":6},{"id":122,"text":"But that proposal ,","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"Mr. Furman said","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"the White House found ,","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"would raise taxes by an average of $ 2,400 on 17 million middle-class households","depth":6},{"id":126,"text":"and would create a serious disincentive for all Americans","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"who hit that threshold","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"to contribute to charities","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"because they wouldn ' t get a tax benefit","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"for doing so .","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"Placing the limit on households","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"making more than $ 250,000","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"would generate only $ 800 billion ,","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"Mr. Furman said ,","depth":5},{"id":135,"text":"and would create an immense \" cliff , \"","depth":5},{"id":136,"text":"in which someone","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"whose income rose to $ 251,000","depth":7},{"id":138,"text":"could suddenly owe thousands of dollars more in taxes .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":277,"left":242,"right":276,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":168,"right":241,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":164,"right":167,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":161,"right":163,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":161,"left":150,"right":160,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":141,"right":149,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":140,"right":2,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":140,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":149,"left":143,"right":148,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":143,"left":142,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":142,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":145,"right":147,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":6,"right":144,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":9,"right":146,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":146,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":160,"left":159,"right":22,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":12,"right":158,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":152,"right":157,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":152,"left":13,"right":151,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":16,"right":156,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":17,"right":155,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":155,"left":18,"right":154,"relati